{
    "publish_date": "2014-03-24T19:00:18.000Z", 
    "score": 0.00013987858538788331, 
    "video_length": "PT5M18S", 
    "captions": [
        {
            "text": "The Tree of Forty Fruit\nis a single fruit tree", 
            "dur": "2.775", 
            "start": "12.617"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that grows over 40 different\nvarieties of stone fruits,", 
            "dur": "2.872", 
            "start": "15.392"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "including peaches, plums,\napricots, nectarines, cherries", 
            "dur": "3.876", 
            "start": "18.264"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and this year we&#39;ll know\nif it grows almonds.", 
            "dur": "3.472", 
            "start": "22.14"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Throughout the majority of the year\nit&#39;s a normal looking fruit tree", 
            "dur": "3.275", 
            "start": "25.612"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "until spring when it blossoms", 
            "dur": "2.447", 
            "start": "28.887"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in all these variegated tones\nof pink and white and crimson.", 
            "dur": "3.698", 
            "start": "31.334"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It returns to an ordinary looking\nfruit tree", 
            "dur": "2.331", 
            "start": "35.032"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "until it starts to grow\n40 different types of fruit.", 
            "dur": "3.341", 
            "start": "37.363"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In order to start this project\nI realized that I needed to collect", 
            "dur": "3.042", 
            "start": "40.704"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "hundreds of varieties of stone fruits.", 
            "dur": "2.095", 
            "start": "43.746"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And after scouring New York\nand finding only a few growers", 
            "dur": "3.645", 
            "start": "45.841"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that were actually growing stone fruits,", 
            "dur": "2.552", 
            "start": "49.486"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I realized the extent to which\nwe&#39;ve created these massive monocultures.", 
            "dur": "4.416", 
            "start": "52.038"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "To give you an example,\nthe majority of stone fruits now", 
            "dur": "2.786", 
            "start": "56.454"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "are grown in the Central Valley\nin California,", 
            "dur": "2.395", 
            "start": "59.24"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "whereas the majority of apples are grown\nin New York and Washington State.", 
            "dur": "3.604", 
            "start": "61.635"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The one place where I was able\nto find stone fruits was at this orchard", 
            "dur": "4.189", 
            "start": "65.239"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "at the New York State\nagriculture experiment station in Geneva.", 
            "dur": "3.292", 
            "start": "69.428"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It turns out that central New York\nduring the 19th century", 
            "dur": "3.229", 
            "start": "72.72"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "was one of the largest producers\nof stone fruits.", 
            "dur": "2.859", 
            "start": "75.949"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And that this one single orchard", 
            "dur": "2.167", 
            "start": "78.808"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "was the 150 to 200 year history", 
            "dur": "2.883", 
            "start": "80.975"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of that industry", 
            "dur": "2.035", 
            "start": "83.858"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and contained all of the heirloom, \nnative, hybrid, and antique varieties.", 
            "dur": "6.973", 
            "start": "85.893"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The problem was is that they were\ngoing to tear this orchard out", 
            "dur": "3.089", 
            "start": "92.866"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "due to a lack of funding.", 
            "dur": "2.743", 
            "start": "95.955"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Up until that point I grew up on a farm,", 
            "dur": "3.433", 
            "start": "98.698"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but I hadn&#39;t really thought\nabout farming for about 20 years,", 
            "dur": "3.344", 
            "start": "102.131"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "until I found out\nthey were going to tear this orchard out.", 
            "dur": "2.8", 
            "start": "105.475"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And for some reason\nI felt that it was a tragedy.", 
            "dur": "2.635", 
            "start": "108.275"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And so I picked up the lease\non the orchard and preserved it", 
            "dur": "3.485", 
            "start": "110.91"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "until I could figure out\nwhat to do with all the varieties.", 
            "dur": "3.171", 
            "start": "114.395"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And so this is my nursery.", 
            "dur": "1.797", 
            "start": "117.566"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I keep dwarf stock trees,\nor what I call stock trees", 
            "dur": "2.943", 
            "start": "119.363"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "where over the past 5 years", 
            "dur": "1.597", 
            "start": "122.306"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I&#39;ve methodically taken\nall of the heirloom,", 
            "dur": "2.733", 
            "start": "123.903"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "antique and native species\nand grafted them onto my trees.", 
            "dur": "3.473", 
            "start": "126.636"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "From there, this nursery also\nis where I grow the Tree of Forty Fruit.", 
            "dur": "4.303", 
            "start": "130.109"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And so I start\nthe Tree of Forty Fruit as rootstock,", 
            "dur": "2.711", 
            "start": "134.412"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "where I take one of the varieties\nfrom one of my stock trees,", 
            "dur": "3.533", 
            "start": "137.123"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "put it onto a root structure.", 
            "dur": "2.286", 
            "start": "140.656"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "After 2 years it&#39;s pruned back\nto create an open center or vase shape", 
            "dur": "3.867", 
            "start": "142.942"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "with 4 or 5 primary branches.", 
            "dur": "1.893", 
            "start": "146.809"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "After two more years\nit looks something like this.", 
            "dur": "3.16", 
            "start": "148.702"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So everywhere where you see white paint", 
            "dur": "3.754", 
            "start": "151.862"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that&#39;s where a different branch is.", 
            "dur": "2.642", 
            "start": "155.616"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The process I use for doing the grafting\nis called &quot;chip grafting&quot;.", 
            "dur": "3.7", 
            "start": "158.258"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And for that I take\na sliver off of one of the trees", 
            "dur": "4.27", 
            "start": "161.958"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that includes the bud.", 
            "dur": "1.758", 
            "start": "166.228"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I insert it a like size incision\nin the working tree, tape it,", 
            "dur": "3.842", 
            "start": "167.986"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "let it sit and heal in all winter", 
            "dur": "2.785", 
            "start": "171.828"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and then I prune it back", 
            "dur": "1.754", 
            "start": "174.613"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and hope that it grows.", 
            "dur": "2.572", 
            "start": "176.367"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "A few more years --", 
            "dur": "1.272", 
            "start": "178.939"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So this is probably\nabout 5 to 6 years total.", 
            "dur": "2.131", 
            "start": "180.211"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The tree looks something like this.", 
            "dur": "1.723", 
            "start": "182.342"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You can see the red branches that indicate\nwhere a different variety grows.", 
            "dur": "3.908", 
            "start": "184.065"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This is how the trees\nare then diagramed.", 
            "dur": "2.379", 
            "start": "187.973"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "They&#39;re all color-coded diagrams", 
            "dur": "1.738", 
            "start": "190.352"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to show you the years and what variety.", 
            "dur": "2.692", 
            "start": "192.09"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So I work with over 250 varieties\nof stone fruit now.", 
            "dur": "2.945", 
            "start": "194.782"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "What I&#39;ve done is I&#39;ve created\nthis sort of comprehensive timeline", 
            "dur": "2.992", 
            "start": "197.727"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of when they blossom\nin relationship to each other.", 
            "dur": "2.784", 
            "start": "200.719"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So that that way I can design", 
            "dur": "2.207", 
            "start": "203.503"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and essentially sculpt the tree\nand how it blossoms.", 
            "dur": "3.598", 
            "start": "205.71"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Eventually those blossoms become fruit.", 
            "dur": "3.099", 
            "start": "209.308"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And so these are plums that I took", 
            "dur": "2.691", 
            "start": "212.407"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "from just one of the Tree of Forty Fruit", 
            "dur": "2.255", 
            "start": "215.098"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in just one week in August.", 
            "dur": "2.068", 
            "start": "217.353"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "For a variety of reasons", 
            "dur": "2.757", 
            "start": "219.421"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we continue to lose variety and diversity", 
            "dur": "2.446", 
            "start": "222.178"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in the fruit that&#39;s available for us.", 
            "dur": "1.924", 
            "start": "224.624"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And working with commercial growers", 
            "dur": "1.985", 
            "start": "226.548"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I found that the rationale in that", 
            "dur": "1.874", 
            "start": "228.533"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and in what varieties are actually grown", 
            "dur": "2.435", 
            "start": "230.407"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is determined by how long it will keep.", 
            "dur": "2.835", 
            "start": "232.842"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The second is the size.", 
            "dur": "1.493", 
            "start": "235.677"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Is it a single serving size?", 
            "dur": "1.795", 
            "start": "237.17"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The third is how is its presentation?", 
            "dur": "3.007", 
            "start": "238.965"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That is the color.", 
            "dur": "1.46", 
            "start": "241.972"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "People generally don&#39;t like a yellow plum.", 
            "dur": "3.193", 
            "start": "243.432"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And then finally,\nafter all that&#39;s considered", 
            "dur": "3.293", 
            "start": "246.625"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is the taste.", 
            "dur": "1.575", 
            "start": "249.918"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That&#39;s the reason why there&#39;s\nthousands of stone fruit varieties,", 
            "dur": "3.257", 
            "start": "251.493"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but yet only a few\nare actually ever seen at a market.", 
            "dur": "3.311", 
            "start": "254.75"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And so I look at the Tree of Forty Fruit", 
            "dur": "2.127", 
            "start": "258.061"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "as an artwork, a research project,", 
            "dur": "2.704", 
            "start": "260.188"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and a form of conservation.", 
            "dur": "1.665", 
            "start": "262.892"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "As an artwork,\nwhat it does is it interrupts", 
            "dur": "2.545", 
            "start": "264.557"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and transforms the everyday.", 
            "dur": "2.083", 
            "start": "267.102"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "As a research project, it creates\none of the first comprehensive time lines", 
            "dur": "3.744", 
            "start": "269.185"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of when all these varieties blossom\nin relationship to each other,", 
            "dur": "3.314", 
            "start": "272.929"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "which becomes important\nwhen we consider pollination.", 
            "dur": "4.172", 
            "start": "276.243"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And finally as a form of conservation,", 
            "dur": "2.908", 
            "start": "280.415"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "by taking all of these heirloom,", 
            "dur": "1.854", 
            "start": "283.323"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "antique and native species,", 
            "dur": "2.194", 
            "start": "285.177"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "grafting them onto\nthe Trees of Forty Fruit", 
            "dur": "2.445", 
            "start": "287.371"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and then placing them\nthroughout the country,", 
            "dur": "2.424", 
            "start": "289.816"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in some small way\nI&#39;m creating my own type", 
            "dur": "3.067", 
            "start": "292.24"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of diversity and preservation.", 
            "dur": "2.646", 
            "start": "295.307"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Thank you.", 
            "dur": "1.162", 
            "start": "297.953"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "(Applause)", 
            "dur": "1.705", 
            "start": "299.115"
        }
    ], 
